# PBAC × Cedar (embedded) — org-defined policies as parameter ENTITIES
# The PO references its governing policy (active, min_amount, max_amount, regions loaded from
# Postgres); amount/region are request-time context on both engines. The amount must sit
# INSIDE the window: below min_amount is petty cash → deny, above max_amount → deny.

@host = http://localhost:8080

### ALLOW — assignee, active policy, amount inside [min,max], region covered
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "pbac",
  "principal": "psn-091613",
  "action": "po.approve",
  "resource_type": "PurchaseOrder",
  "resource": "po-000160",
  "context": { "amount": 357662180, "region": "bandung" }
}

### DENY — same assignee, PO and amount, but the region is NOT in the policy's list
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "pbac",
  "principal": "psn-091613",
  "action": "po.approve",
  "resource_type": "PurchaseOrder",
  "resource": "po-000160",
  "context": { "amount": 357662180, "region": "medan" }
}

### Playground — drop the amount below the policy floor (petty cash) to see the deny
POST {{host}}/v1/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "engine": "cedar",
  "model": "pbac",
  "principal": "psn-091613",
  "action": "po.approve",
  "resource_type": "PurchaseOrder",
  "resource": "po-000160",
  "context": { "amount": 1, "region": "bandung" }
}
